      "date": "2018-11-30 22:40:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs there a test case for this?\n\nAt least add a few lines of tests to see if the original problem is still hit:\n\n Test-Parameters: testlist=sanity-quota,sanity-quota,sanity-quota\n\nUnfortunately, the test only failed 40/759 runs (about 0.5%) so running 200 full sanity-quota test runs is probably too much for autotest (that would be 200h of testing).\n\nRunning a local loop for that test would be more useful, but would still take about 4.5h to run.  It wouldn't be too hard to add a fortestonly patch on top of this one with the following change in sanity-quota.sh:\n\n for i in {1..400}; do\n       run test_1\n done\n\nThat would run the test in a loop, but would not be for landing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
